d-flex\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#ZdExportPDFModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531554\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531554\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 06, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104reh1665702740792.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/reh1665702740792.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/reh1665702740792.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"reh1665702740792\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                             \n Connect the Uniface Router Monitor to the Uniface Router\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can connect a single Router Monitor to only one Uniface Router at a time. However,\n      it is possible to have multiple Monitors connected to a single Uniface Router.</p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"reh1665702740792__context_w2412ab1b5b1_w2413ab1b5_w2414ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"reh1665702740792__topic_d31361e1_d31362e1_d31363e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"reh1665702740792__p_d31364e1_d31365e1_d31366e1\">Use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$MAXMONS</span> assignment\n               setting in <span class=\"ph filepath\">urouter.asn</span> to specify the number of Router Monitors\n               allowed to connect to the Uniface Router.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"reh1665702740792__p_d31367e1_d31368e1_d31369e1\">To connect the Uniface Router Monitor to a Uniface Router:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"reh1665702740792__li_d16067e1_d16068e1_d16069e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Start the Uniface Router Monitor.\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"reh1665702740792__li_d16070e1_d16071e1_d16072e1\">By default, the Connect dialog is displayed, but this behavior can be altered by editing the monitor settings.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"reh1665702740792__li_d16073e1_d16074e1_d16075e1\">If the Router Monitor is running but not\n                     connected, choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">URouter &gt; Connect</span></span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"reh1665702740792__li_d16076e1_d16077e1_d16078e1\">If you are already connected and want to\n                     connect to another Uniface Router, choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">URouter &gt; Disconnect</span></span>, then choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">URouter &gt; Connect</span></span>. </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"reh1665702740792__li_d16079e1_d16080e1_d16081e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"reh1665702740792__p_d31370e1_d31371e1_d31372e1\">In the Connect dialog, provide the following\n               information:</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"reh1665702740792__table_d3233e1_d3234e1_d3235e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Uniface Router Monitor Connection Fields</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"reh1665702740792__table_d3233e1_d3234e1_d3235e1__entry__1\">Field</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"reh1665702740792__table_d3233e1_d3234e1_d3235e1__entry__2\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"reh1665702740792__table_d3233e1_d3234e1_d3235e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Hostname</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"reh1665702740792__table_d3233e1_d3234e1_d3235e1__entry__2\">Identifier of the host on which the\n                              Uniface Router is running; for example, <code class=\"ph codeph\">localhost</code> or\n                                 <code class=\"ph codeph\">LABHOST-PC0001</code>, or an IP address.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"reh1665702740792__table_d3233e1_d3234e1_d3235e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Network protocol</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"reh1665702740792__table_d3233e1_d3234e1_d3235e1__entry__2\">Network protocol used to connect the\n                              Router Monitor to the Uniface Router: <code class=\"ph codeph\">TCP</code> or\n                                 <code class=\"ph codeph\">TLS</code>. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"reh1665702740792__table_d3233e1_d3234e1_d3235e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Address / port</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"reh1665702740792__table_d3233e1_d3234e1_d3235e1__entry__2\">Address or port on the host that the\n                              Uniface Router is listening to. By default, this is 13001. <div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"reh1665702740792__note_w2418ab1b5b3b3b3b1b3b7b5b3b1_w2419ab1b5b3b3b3b1b3b7b5b3_w2420ab1b5b3b3b3b1b3b7b5_w2421ab1b5b3b3b3b1b3b7_w2422ab1b5b3b3b3b1b3_w2423ab1b5b3b3b3b1_w2424ab1b5b3b3b3_w2425ab1b5b3b3_w2426ab1b5b3_w2427ab1b5_w2428ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> You can append a TLS profile to the port number to\n                                 specify an explicit (non-default) profile. For more information,\n                                 see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zwe1665702525639.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zwe1665702525639.html\" title=\"A TLS connection profile is a named collection of TLS connector options that can be used to define multiple connections to Uniface Routers and Uniface Servers, each with its own configuration.\">TLS Connection Profiles</a>.</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"reh1665702740792__table_d3233e1_d3234e1_d3235e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Become privileged user</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"reh1665702740792__table_d3233e1_d3234e1_d3235e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">If selected, the following fields are displayed:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"reh1665702740792__li_d16082e1_d16083e1_d16084e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Username</span>—user name must be the same as\n                                    the account under which the Uniface Router is running, or\n                                       ‘<code class=\"ph codeph\">UROUTER</code>’. If TCP is used, it is not hidden,\n                                    scrambled, or encoded. If TLS is used, the information is\n                                    protected.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"reh1665702740792__li_d16085e1_d16086e1_d16087e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Password</span>—It is not scrambled or encoded,\n                                    but is replaced by ‘<code class=\"ph codeph\">***</code>’ in the forms where it\n                                    appears. See also <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"prv1665702740862.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/prv1665702740862.html\" title=\"Specify the privileged user account under which the Uniface Router runs and which can be used to start and stop Uniface Routers and Servers using the Uniface Router Monitor or the UROUTMON component.\">$PRIV_MON_USER</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"reh1665702740792__note_w2429ab1b5b3b3b3b1b3b7b7b3b5_w2430ab1b5b3b3b3b1b3b7b7b3_w2431ab1b5b3b3b3b1b3b7b7_w2432ab1b5b3b3b3b1b3b7_w2433ab1b5b3b3b3b1b3_w2434ab1b5b3b3b3b1_w2435ab1b5b3b3b3_w2436ab1b5b3b3_w2437ab1b5b3_w2438ab1b5_w2439ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The user name and password will be authenticated on\n                                 the machine running the Uniface Router, so they must represent a\n                                 valid account on that machine.</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"reh1665702740792__p_d31373e1_d31374e1_d31375e1\">To specify the default values for these fields,\n                  see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pls1665702740931.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pls1665702740931.html\" title=\"To control the behavior of the Uniface Router Monitor, you can edit the monitor preferences.\">Specify Preferences for the Uniface Router Monitor</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"section result body required-cleanup-multiple-ol-elements-in-topic-body\" id=\"reh1665702740792__result_w2415ab1b5b5_w2416ab1b5_w2417ab1\">\n<div class=\"sectiondiv result\" id=\"reh1665702740792__topic_d31376e1_d31377e1_d31378e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"reh1665702740792__p_d31379e1_d31380e1_d31381e1\">If the Uniface Router is not running, or if it is listening to a different port number, the Router Monitor cannot make a connection.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qyk1665702738023.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface Router Monitor</a><p>The Uniface Router Monitor is a Uniface Windows application that you can use to fine-tune the performance of the Uniface Router while it is running.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/exm1665702529212.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface Router</a><p>The Uniface Router is a multi-threaded process (urouter) responsible for interprocess communication in Uniface applications. It listens for requests from Uniface client applications and routes them to the appropriate Uniface Server, and it passes messages between various Uniface applications.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ihz1665702529113.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$MAX_MONS</a><p>Specify the maximum number of Uniface Router Monitors that the Uniface Router can accept.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531554\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531554\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Connect the Uniface Router Monitor to the Uniface Router Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 06, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Connect the Uniface Router Monitor to the Uniface Router You can connect a single Router Monitor to only one Uniface Router at a time. However, it is possible to have multiple Monitors connected to a single Uniface Router. Use the $MAXMONS assignment setting in urouter.asn to specify the number of Router Monitors allowed to connect to the Uniface Router. To connect the Uniface Router Monitor to a Uniface Router: Start the Uniface Router Monitor. By default, the Connect dialog is displayed, but this behavior can be altered by editing the monitor settings. If the Router Monitor is running but not connected, choose URouter > Connect If you are already connected and want to connect to another Uniface Router, choose URouter > Disconnect , then choose URouter > Connect . In the Connect dialog, provide the following information: Table 1. Uniface Router Monitor Connection Fields Field Description Hostname Identifier of the host on which the Uniface Router is running; for example, localhost or LABHOST-PC0001 , or an IP address. Network protocol Network protocol used to connect the Router Monitor to the Uniface Router: TCP or TLS . Address / port Address or port on the host that the Uniface Router is listening to. By default, this is 13001. Note: You can append a TLS profile to the port number to specify an explicit (non-default) profile. For more information, see TLS Connection Profiles . Become privileged user If selected, the following fields are displayed: Username —user name must be the same as the account under which the Uniface Router is running, or ‘ UROUTER ’. If TCP is used, it is not hidden, scrambled, or encoded. If TLS is used, the information is protected. Password —It is not scrambled or encoded, but is replaced by ‘ *** ’ in the forms where it appears. See also $PRIV_MON_USER . Note: The user name and password will be authenticated on the machine running the Uniface Router, so they must represent a valid account on that machine. To specify the default values for these fields, see Specify Preferences for the Uniface Router Monitor . If the Uniface Router is not running, or if it is listening to a different port number, the Router Monitor cannot make a connection. Related Links Uniface Router Monitor The Uniface Router Monitor is a Uniface Windows application that you can use to fine-tune the performance of the Uniface Router while it is running. Uniface Router The Uniface Router is a multi-threaded process (urouter) responsible for interprocess communication in Uniface applications. It listens for requests from Uniface client applications and routes them to the appropriate Uniface Server, and it passes messages between various Uniface applications. $MAX_MONS Specify the maximum number of Uniface Router Monitors that the Uniface Router can accept. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}